column_.text_: What is that?
Oh no... The city's falling to pieces...
Hey... I think we need to tell Zathba about Rolan...
We finally got Lyria back, but this doesn't bode well.
Look at the color of that sky... It makes my hair stand on end.
Hey! It's Mr. Shades!
Well, what do we have here?
Oh, and you folks got your friend back.
H-hello, nice to meet you. My name is Lyria!

I'm Zathba, an information broker. It musta been tough out there,
eh, little lady?
Um, yes... It was...
Zathba, do not frighten the poor child.
Huh? Who's being scary? I'm on my best behavior here.
It pleases me to see that everyone is in good health.

I came to lend my support the moment I caught wind of Avia's
assault on Seedhollow.
Speaking of allies, I don't see Rolan with you. Where'd he go?
He's been captured.
He needs our help.
He's been captured.
He's been captured.
Crap. Well, look. Don't get too down. He's not one to croak without a fight.
He needs our help.
He needs our help.

Your eyes tell me more than words can convey. It must have been a
horrific affair.
Maybe we can do something for him though.
You in, Histy?
Most certainly. I am off to make arrangements at once.
All right...

Call it intuition, or an overactive gut, but an epic storm's brewing in
this here skydom.
Don't know how to explain it, but the air's buzzing with emotions.

Stuff like joy, anxiety, sadness, anger... You can tell when it's
coming to a head.

I haven't felt this spooked since the Dahli Island disaster fifteen
years ago.
My point is you folks oughta haul it back to your own skydom.
What? You can't say that at a time like this!
Look, my sources tell me you hail from Phantagrande.

You've got a fine ship that can cross the Grim Basin. No need to
play hero here.

It's not like that. We can't just leave everyone when we know
what's coming.

Lilith is going to use something called the Pillar of Vayoi to destroy
the sky! Do we just let her do it?
And what about Rolan!

Let me be the voice of reason here. You saved your "princess."
Mission accomplished.

So what do knights do after rescuing the damsel? They make sure
she stays safe.

You're an excellent captain, so I don't need to spell out your next
move for you, do I?

You're an excellent captain, so I don't need to spell out your next
move for you, do I?
We're gonna save Rolan.
I appreciate the concern.
We're gonna save Rolan.
We're gonna save Rolan.

I'm glad you're looking out for the man, but did you hear a single
word I said?
I appreciate the concern.
I appreciate the concern.
Well, your crew's grown on me. That's why we'll take it from here.
Come on. All I'm saying is don't push your luck.
(Aw, who am I kidding? We both know I can't talk you outta this.)
(But Zegagrande is our home. At least let us keep our pride.)

Be seein' you around then. And quit with the long faces. We
can handle this.
Zathba told us we should get out of Zegagrande, but...

Rolan made it abundantly clear that Angra Mainyu is more
than Zegagrande's problem.
That power can and will consume the skies.
Exactly. Um, so... What I wanted to say was...

We got you, Lyria. Just take a look at . Is that the face of
somebody fixing to run away?

We got you, Lyria. Just take a look at . Is that the face of
somebody fixing to run away?
Oh.
No, it isn't! Hehe.

We're headin' into endgame territory. If you've got any
unfinished business, now's the time!

Ready to strike out for the docks? Bet the Grandcypher's
getting lonely.
Curses! What have we been fighting for this whole time?
Sir... What's going to happen to Avia?

Lady Lilith said—ugh, forget it. She's no leader. Not after what
she's done.

How many of our comrades did she send to the grave without a
second thought?
That's her idea of salvation? We were lambs led to the slaughter.

We took up the sword to prevent this very scenario from
happening.
Sir...
Excuse me...
Hm?
The shaman!
I'm so relieved to see that you're safe.
Oh, no-no-no! I... I'm not the shaman anymore...
Ah...

We treated you terribly, to put it lightly. On behalf of my unit, I
sincerely apologize.

Although we were following Lilith's orders, it was our choice to
carry them out.
What's done is done.
It's Lilith's fault.
What's done is done.
What's done is done.
You're too kind...
It's Lilith's fault.
It's Lilith's fault.

True, but that doesn't excuse our blind faith. We have to reflect on
our actions.

I'm not looking to buy your forgiveness, but I do wish to offer
recompense if I can.
I'd be happy to answer any questions you might have.
Tell me about Id.
Tell me about Gallanza.
Tell me about Maglielle.
I'm fine.
Tell me about Id.
Tell me about Id.
Id is Lilith's only son and sole bodyguard.

He's way above my pay grade. I hear he gets sent on secret
missions when not on duty.

There's something about him that rubs people the wrong way. He's
impersonal, to say the least.
But occasionally he'll get this look of sadness on his face.

Something from his past, maybe? I never had the chance to speak
with him, so that's all I know.
Tell me about Gallanza.
Tell me about Gallanza.

Gallanza leads the Silver Wolf Corps, and he's a demon with the
spear.

Every fiber of his being is dedicated to strength, and I say that
without hyperbole.

Legend has it he crushed the competition at Zega's premier fighting
tournament ages ago.
The fabled Astrals of Estalucia are next on his list, or so I’ve heard.
Tell me about Maglielle.
Tell me about Maglielle.
Magus Maglielle is the stately leader of the Sword Veil Fellowship.

It's a special forces unit whose members fight by levitating their
weapons.

Rumor has it she was chased from her home because people
viewed her magic as heresy.
Her overwhelming power cast her as a pariah, or so it would seem.

Thus she hopes the land of Estalucia will provide respite for her and
her followers.
I'm fine.
I'm fine.
Very well.
We pray to these skies for your safety.

Ah, welcome back. The Grandcypher's good to go. Are you ready to
leave?
Let's fly.
We still need some time to prepare.
Let's fly.
Let's fly.
We still need some time to prepare.
We still need some time to prepare.

Take all the time you need, bud... This is one mission we can not
screw up.

Take all the time you need, bud... This is one mission we can not
screw up.
The air currents have become unstable. Keep your wits about you.
So... are we really doin' this? What's the plan?
We're going to rescue Rolan.
We're going to save the world.
We're going to rescue Rolan.
We're going to rescue Rolan.
Hehe! Right on! Mission numero uno!

He's the reason we were able to save Lyria. Now it's our turn to
repay the favor.
'N I gotta thank him for takin' such good care of the Grandcypher.
I'm with ya there, but this ain't gonna be a walk in the park, y'know.
Heh, bring it on. There's no turnin' back anyway!
We're going to save the world.
We're going to save the world.
Anything's possible if we work together!

Think of all the people we've met in this skydom, the precious
memories we've made. We will protect Zegagrande.

Defying an Astral and a forbidden primal beast. Quite the mess
we've stumbled into.

Too late now for second guesses, right? Whatever happens, we just
have to win!
Hang tight, Fix It Dude. We're a-comin' for ya!
Let's give it everything we've got!
Heh! A more fearless crew, there never was.
Hah. Let us wish them well.

They're the perfect folks to defy primeval gods. Kinda glad it's them
and not me.
And so our debt to them grows heavier once more.
Well, enough yammering. We got our own work to do!

Wind's running wild today! But it's nothing the Grandcypher
can't handle!
Oh man... Ready or not, guys... This is it!

Hey, this is Rolan's. He must've dropped it during all that
hubbub at the castle.
Be sure you return it to him whenever he gets back, eh?

We finally have Lyria back, but there's not even time to
celebrate.

We finally have Lyria back, but there's not even time to
celebrate.

Lilith is so close to her goal; she's become blind to
everything else. I doubt there's anything that can stop her
now—except us.

Lilith is so close to her goal; she's become blind to
everything else. I doubt there's anything that can stop her
now—except us.

It might sound melodramatic, but this is fate. Our crew
versus Lilith.

It might sound melodramatic, but this is fate. Our crew
versus Lilith.

So there's only one thing left to do—fly to the Pillar of Vayoi,
and end this.

So there's only one thing left to do—fly to the Pillar of Vayoi,
and end this.
